@node "HowToInstall" "Installation"

@{MS "Installation"}

Just use the included installer script to install this application!@{par}

@{b}Don't try to install this archive by hand, because this may cause many trouble. The automatic installation
ensures a minimum use of disc and memory space!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "QuickStart" "How to use IRComRemote"

@{MS "How to use IRComRemote"}


@{b}Before you start this application you should ensure then the IRCom
Driverpacket is installed and configured.@{ub}@{par}

After installation perform a reboot or start @{b}IRComRemoteServer@{ub} by clicking on it's icon.@{par}

Now start @{b}IRComRemote@{ub} and a window with a list view gadget and a few buttons appears.

@{MT "Step 1"}

Choose @{b}new@{ub} in this main window and another window the @{"IRComRemote Set-Up" link "Edit"} is
opening. At top of the window there is a text input field named IR-Key which contains two
'\@'. Here the IR-Key name needs to be specified in IRCom-Format. Well, you
could do this, but it's easier to simply push the key on your remote. The text
field fills automaticaly with the correct string.@{par}

@{MT "Step 2"}

Now only a name is missing. The name is only for display in the main list and
for you to remember it's function. Of course you need to setup an execution type
and the command. Specific information on what is possible can be found
@{"hier" link "EditComm"}.@{par}

@{MT "Step 3"}

Now push the @{b}use@{ub} gadget for return to the main window. Now
@{b}save@{ub} settings and the window gets closed. The IRComRemoteServer takes
over again. Press the configured key on your remote like you did previously
during set-up and the action takes place.

@endnode
