@node "MAST" "IRComRemote - Main set-up"

@{MS "Main set-up"}

Well, there isn't much to say! Use the cursor keys for selecting and the return key for entering
the @{"hotkey set-up" link "Edit"}.@{par}

Here're the gadgets of the preferences program:@{par}
@{code}
@{MS "Miscellaneous set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Global Set-Up" link "MASTGlob"}
@{MS "IRComRemote set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"IRComRemote List" link "MASTLIST"}
@{"New..." link "MASTNEWI"}
@{"Copy..." link "MASTCOPY"}
@{"Edit..." link "MASTEDIT"}
@{"Remove..." link "MASTDELE"}

@{"Save" link "MASTSAVE"}
@{"Use" link "MASTOKOK"}
@{"Cancel" link "MASTCANC"}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@{"Main Window" link "MAsT"} @{"Edit Window" link "Edit"} @{"Global Set-Up" link "Glob"}

@endnode
@node "MASTGlob" "IRComRemote - Global Set-up..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Global Set-up..."}

This button opens the @{"IRComRemote Set-up" link "Glob"} window.@{par}

@endnode
@node "MASTLIST" "Main Set-up - The IRComRemote List"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "The IRComRemote List"}

This list contains all user defined IR-keys. By pressing return or using the
@{"edit" link "MASTEDIT"} gadget you are able to @{"edit" link "Edit"} the current entry.
The @{"new" link "MASTNEWI"} gadget allows to add a new entry and the @{"remove" link "MASTDELE"} gadget
allows to delete the active one!

@endnode
@node "MASTNEWI" "Main Set-up - New..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "New..."}

Creates a new entry and opens the @{"IRComRemote Set-up" link "Edit"} window for the new item.@{par}

@{b}Aborting the @{"IRComRemote Set-up" link "Edit"} window causes the new entry to be removed.@{ub}@{par}


@endnode
@node "MASTCOPY" "Main Set-up - Copy..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Copy..."}

This button clones the current entry and opens the @{"IRComRemote Set-up" link "Edit"} window.

@{b}Aborting the @{"IRComRemote Set-up" link "Edit"} window causes the new entry to be removed.@{ub}@{par}


@endnode
@node "MASTEDIT" "Main Set-up - Edit..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Edit..."}

By pressing on this button the @{"edit" link "Edit"} window opens and allows you to change the
IRComRemote settings.

@endnode
@node "MASTDELE" "Main Set-up - Remove..."
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Remove..."}

After a safety request the selected item will be removed from list!

@endnode
@node "MASTSave" "Main Set-up - Save"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Save"}

The settings will be saved into IRComRemoteServer icon and used as well. The hotkey configuration will be
stored in the ENV: directory. All IRComRemote windows will close immediately.

@endnode
@node "MASTOkOk" "Main Set-up - Use"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Use"}

The window will be closed and the settings used, but the settings won't be saved!

@endnode
@node "MASTCanc" "Main Set-up - Cancel"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Cancel"}

This button closes the window and all changed settings are lost!

@endnode

@node "Edit" "IRComRemote - IRComRemote Set-up"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "IRComRemote Set-up"}

This window allows to set-up a IR-Key actions. Just press the desired key on
your remote to inject it into the configuration.@{par}

Now you just need to define a execution type and a command to use it.@{par}

@{code}
@{MS "Key Set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Name" link "EditName"}
@{"IR-Key" link "EDITIRNA"}
@{"Task" link "EditTask"}
@{MS "Command Set-up"}
@{JCENTER}@{"Execute Type" link "EditExTy"}
@{"Stack" link "EditStac"}
@{"Command" link "EditComm"}
@{"Current Directory" link "EditCuDi"}
@{"Output File" link "EditOuFi"}
@{"Use" link "EditOkOk"}
@{"Cancel" link "EditCanc"}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@{"Main Window" link "MAsT"} @{"Edit Window" link "Edit"} @{"Global Set-Up" link "Glob"}

@endnode
@node "EditName" "IRComRemote Set-up - Name"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Name"}

Here you can specify a special name for the IR-key@{par}

The name will only be used for the @{"IRComRemote list" link "MASTLIST"}!

@endnode
@node "EDITIRNA" "IRComRemote Set-up - IR-Key"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "IR-Key"}

Here you can specify the ir-key in IRCom Format. A more easy way is to simply
press the desired button on your remote.

@endnode
@node "EditTask" "IRComRemote Set-up - Task"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Task"}

By using this gadget you can bind an IR-key to a specific task. By doing this the same IR-key
can be used in different programs to cause different action.@{par}

IRComRemote is comparing from the end of the task name. If you specify "golded" it
will match with "t:golded" as well as with a task named "golded:golded"@{par}

The easiest way to specify task is to use the pop up gadget next to the input
field and select the task name from list. Many known and non use tasks are
removed and others are simplified to make selections as easy as possible.@{par}

A IR-key without a task gets active if non other identical IR-key is matching
with a task. E.g. there are two IR-keys with the name IR signal. One has the
task "Golded", the other hasn't a task specified. The IR-key with "golded" gets
only active in GoldED. The other gets active in any other situation.@{par}

@endnode
@node "EditExTy" "IRComRemote Set-up - Execute type"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Execute type"}

This gadget allows to set-up what type of command is specified in the @{"command" link "EditComm"} gadget.@{par}

Currently "CLI", "WB", "Key", "Arexx" and @{"Macro" link "Macros"} are available.@{par}

@endnode
@node "EditStac" "IRComRemote Set-up - Stack"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Stack"}

This gadget specifies the stack for the @{"command" link "EditComm"}.

@endnode
@node "EditComm" "IRComRemote Set-up - Command"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Command"}

The contents of this gadget depends on the @{"execute type" link "EditExTy"}:

@{MT "CLI / WB / ARexx"}

Path and command name of the command you want to execute.

@{MT "Key"}

This gadget contains a new key combination. Please note that key groups like "SHIFT" are not
allowed. It's required to specify the key. So define "LSHIFT", "RSHIFT" or "CAPSLOCK" instead.@{par}

IRComRemote is using the qualifier without any modifications. So a "CONTROL LALT HELP" is used even
if the user is pressing the shift key! Sometimes it may be useful to let the user qualifier through.
Let's say you want the Help key as a replacement for an "a". It's required that you're able to type
a "A" (shift) or an "ć" (alt). The "-" version of a qualifier in indicating that the specified
qualifier is path through. In our case the key command looks like this: "-LSHIFT -RSHIFT -LALT -RALT
-RCOMMAND -RCOMMAND -CONTROL -CAPSLOCK a".

@{MT "Macro"}

IRComRemote is supporting a lot of @{"Macro" link "Macros"}-functions for usage,
which can be selected via a popup list, too.@{par}

@endnode
@node "EditCuDi" "IRComRemote Set-up - Current Directory"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Current Directory"}

If you want to change the current directory for the @{"command" link "EditComm"}, then put it in
here.

@endnode
@node "EditOuFi" "IRComRemote Set-up - Output File"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Output File"}

The output of the command can be redirected by using this gadget.

@endnode
@node "EditOkOk" "IRComRemote Set-up - Use"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Use"}

The hotkey settings will be used and the edit window will be closed.

@endnode
@node "EditCanc" "IRComRemote Set-up - Cancel"
@toc "Edit"

@{MS "Cancel"}

Closes the edit window! All changes will be rejected.

@endnode

@node "Glob" "IRComRemote - Global Set-up"
@toc "MAST"

@{MS "Global Set-up"}

This window allows to configurate the global IRComRemote set-up.@{par}
@{code}
@{MS "Miscellaneous Set-up"}
@{JCENTER}
@{MS "Qualifier Set-up"}
@{JCENTER}
@{"Use" link "GlobOkOk"}
@{"Cancel" link "GlobCanc"}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@{"Main Window" link "MAsT"} @{"Edit Window" link "Edit"} @{"Global Set-Up" link "Glob"}

@endnode
@node "GlobOkOk" "Global Set-up - Use"
@toc "Glob"

@{MS "Use"}

The global settings will be used.

@endnode
@node "GlobCanc" "Global Set-up - Cancel"
@toc "Glob"

@{MS "Cancel"}

Closes the window! All changes will be rejected.

@endnode

@node "GeLw" "The List Selection Window"

@{MS "The List Selection Window"}

This window allows to select a specific entry of a given list.@{par}

@endnode

@node "Macros" "Macros"

@{MS "Macros"}

Macros are small functions, which can be specified as action by a simple
selection.@{par}

@{JCenter}
The following Macros are supported:@{par}

@{b}Screen Operations@{ub}@{par}

@{"ScreenNext" link "MacrosScreenNext"}*@{par}
